	 ('1d501c9f-8dc8-4478-8b26-2acdd29e2527'::uuid,'WRIGHT BROTHERS’ FIRST POWERED BIPLANE','DEVICE','{}','First fully operational aircraft built and flown by the Wrights in 1903, reported and photographed but not widely known initially','{}','{}','{"frequency": 1, "text_unit_ids": ["ee745461b2211d842e88d29f225a86ba7063e293122d56b41cea0528892369a6d28a8de8ecaaba49f767d0dc0952376d919da861f26599624546ddc82d9781c5"]}','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','history_development_aeronautics'),
	 ('880bec98-16dd-4834-9347-32b55a894c98'::uuid,'BLERIOT','PERSON','{}','BLERIOT was a renowned French aviator known for his pioneering aerial achievements. He crossed the English Channel in a monoplane, inspired and influenced by the Wright brothers'' demonstration tours to Europe. According to historical accounts, B陵iot visited the Wright brothers during their European tours, which undoubtedly fueled his ambition to achieve significant milestones in aviation. This visit further solidified his resolve to build upon the Wrights’ advancements and demonstrate that air travel was not only possible but could be accomplished using lighter-than-air technology. The flight over the English Channel in 1909 by B陵iot marked a pivotal moment, confirming Europe''s acceptance of aviation as a viable mode of transportation and signaling the rapid advancement of aeroplane design. Through his daring and innovative spirit, B陵iot played a crucial role in advancing the fledgling field of aviation, leaving an indelible mark on the early history of flying machines.','{}','{}','{"frequency": 2, "text_unit_ids": ["ee745461b2211d842e88d29f225a86ba7063e293122d56b41cea0528892369a6d28a8de8ecaaba49f767d0dc0952376d919da861f26599624546ddc82d9781c5", "ee745461b2211d842e88d29f225a86ba7063e293122d56b41cea0528892369a6d28a8de8ecaaba49f767d0dc0952376d919da861f26599624546ddc82d9781c5"]}','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','history_development_aeronautics'),
	 ('b00b662e-410c-425c-8707-c05ad70f9c18'::uuid,'ENGINE','DEVICE','{}','An engine generates thrust and powers aircraft as described in Wright brothers'' experiments','{}','{}','{"frequency": 1, "text_unit_ids": ["a9ae9046c84bd485f66f44763948025a4066f10073bee095a4c15c4665d9db3e9ee4c83182db236d7659a96a72f09b4262666709a85154db90a6633d796a8eab"]}','2026-07-17 16:18:55.489892','2026-07-17 16:18:55.489892','aerodynamics_v1'),
	 ('f8f444e7-bff1-40af-8290-176e6de37b48'::uuid,'NEWTON','PERSON','{}','Isaac Newton, an eminent English polymath active during the scientific revolution of the 17th century, made significant contributions to various fields including mathematics, physics, astronomy, and alchemy. As a key figure in this pivotal era of scientific advancement, Newton furthered experimental approaches by collaborating with colleagues, particularly focusing on reducing resistance in moving objects. His comprehensive work includes developing the fundamental laws of motion and establishing the theory of universal gravitation. Through his multifaceted explorations and innovations, Newton played an indispensable role in shaping contemporary understanding across these disciplines.','{}','{}','{"frequency": 3, "text_unit_ids": ["5b2cda8d5bbd5d82e2c6fdbd3f95d22ccf5c61786e126e8b0c5e7391999cff6606a62534e3cc3ff179c861f6e0cb19ee489f79b583fb0cfba038d14349b9403b", "5b2cda8d5bbd5d82e2c6fdbd3f95d22ccf5c61786e126e8b0c5e7391999cff6606a62534e3cc3ff179c861f6e0cb19ee489f79b583fb0cfba038d14349b9403b", "420bf471d6efd14f20451de42dd132dbbb1f30032fe7872183bfede6d0e70d8eb4713e527c05d323ff76f0721a4d224b6eb876f0522c8f248b177d4af5b3a251"]}','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','history_development_aeronautics'),
	 ('65a7d0c9-65f3-4fca-b398-a9a881d85c6a'::uuid,'HARGRAVE','PERSON','{}','HARGRAVE''s creation of the box kite in 1895 significantly influenced early aircraft design and testing, demonstrating innovative approaches to aerodynamics that were later adopted by other manufacturers. His work leveraged practical applications of his research, contributing substantially to advancements in aerial technology during the late 19th century. Notably, HARGRAVE''s experiments aligned with similar objectives set forth by Otto Lilienthal, focusing on the application of aerodynamic principles to enable more efficient and controllable flight mechanisms. Through these endeavors, HARGRAVE’s methodologies played a crucial role in shaping subsequent developments in aviation technology.','{}','{}','{"frequency": 4, "text_unit_ids": ["5b2cda8d5bbd5d82e2c6fdbd3f95d22ccf5c61786e126e8b0c5e7391999cff6606a62534e3cc3ff179c861f6e0cb19ee489f79b583fb0cfba038d14349b9403b", "5b2cda8d5bbd5d82e2c6fdbd3f95d22ccf5c61786e126e8b0c5e7391999cff6606a62534e3cc3ff179c861f6e0cb19ee489f79b583fb0cfba038d14349b9403b", "573d5db6e587374521f111a47eaa08e2ce573235b08716d91bbe053504fe503530293339ede873a3ac356c3d376fcb97e005ef76112125385fa9e127d8e42fec", "573d5db6e587374521f111a47eaa08e2ce573235b08716d91bbe053504fe503530293339ede873a3ac356c3d376fcb97e005ef76112125385fa9e127d8e42fec"]}','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','history_development_aeronautics'),
