	 ('c05b14dc-4116-4dca-a804-a8e13c5221e5'::uuid,'JUAN','PERSON','{}','"Juan conducted experiments in 1771 and later to measure forces, particularly on sails, in natural wind conditions."','{}','{}','{"frequency": 2, "text_unit_ids": ["573d5db6e587374521f111a47eaa08e2ce573235b08716d91bbe053504fe503530293339ede873a3ac356c3d376fcb97e005ef76112125385fa9e127d8e42fec", "573d5db6e587374521f111a47eaa08e2ce573235b08716d91bbe053504fe503530293339ede873a3ac356c3d376fcb97e005ef76112125385fa9e127d8e42fec"]}','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','history_development_aeronautics'),
	 ('961701a9-1b5d-4d29-9fda-6723220d0763'::uuid,'CROCE-SPINELLI','PERSON','{}','The entity "CROCE-SPINELLI" refers to a set of tests conducted by an individual or group named Croce-Spinelli in 1874. These tests were instrumental in advancing the knowledge about drag, as they contributed additional information beyond what was previously known. Furthermore, it is also noted that these experiments likely explored other aerodynamic properties using alternative methods or with different body types. This work underscores the importance of early attempts to understand and measure air resistance and the dynamics involved in fluid flow around objects, thus laying foundational research that has since informed various fields including aircraft design and meteorology.','{}','{}','{"frequency": 2, "text_unit_ids": ["573d5db6e587374521f111a47eaa08e2ce573235b08716d91bbe053504fe503530293339ede873a3ac356c3d376fcb97e005ef76112125385fa9e127d8e42fec", "573d5db6e587374521f111a47eaa08e2ce573235b08716d91bbe053504fe503530293339ede873a3ac356c3d376fcb97e005ef76112125385fa9e127d8e42fec"]}','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','history_development_aeronautics'),
	 ('a7165100-3c07-4419-9575-b40c951a8a05'::uuid,'DESDOUT & RICOUR','GROUP','{}','"These individuals together measured pressure distributions in 1886 with bodies mounted on trains. Their contribution helps us understand the challenges and refinements needed in towing experiments for precise aerodynamic data collection."','{}','{}','{"frequency": 2, "text_unit_ids": ["573d5db6e587374521f111a47eaa08e2ce573235b08716d91bbe053504fe503530293339ede873a3ac356c3d376fcb97e005ef76112125385fa9e127d8e42fec", "573d5db6e587374521f111a47eaa08e2ce573235b08716d91bbe053504fe503530293339ede873a3ac356c3d376fcb97e005ef76112125385fa9e127d8e42fec"]}','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','history_development_aeronautics'),
	 ('f5bc838b-8892-41be-bf29-2a61280e364d'::uuid,'GOUPIL','PERSON','{}','GOUPIL conducted experiments with tethered birds in 1884 that significantly advanced the understanding of aerodynamics in natural settings. These experiments involved measuring lift and drag forces under free-wind conditions, crucial elements in the study of avian flight without the use of artificial support structures. Goupil''s work contributed substantially to early research in this field by providing empirical data that helped elucidate fundamental principles of aerodynamics as observed in nature.','{}','{}','{"frequency": 2, "text_unit_ids": ["573d5db6e587374521f111a47eaa08e2ce573235b08716d91bbe053504fe503530293339ede873a3ac356c3d376fcb97e005ef76112125385fa9e127d8e42fec", "573d5db6e587374521f111a47eaa08e2ce573235b08716d91bbe053504fe503530293339ede873a3ac356c3d376fcb97e005ef76112125385fa9e127d8e42fec"]}','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','history_development_aeronautics'),
	 ('8a7207eb-21c7-43ab-bbb0-546f624d1bc7'::uuid,'SMEATON''S MEASUREMENTS','MODEL','{}','Key contributions to whirling arm technology and its applications in measuring drag on various surfaces','{}','{}','{"frequency": 1, "text_unit_ids": ["55e473f9ecac8cd67790067e6eab0198e01f4defc514be87f835b5c567883e65d857bb0c55de712e20d7bed24782b9a7ad7f49d93a4ae738a71114a86c61a98d"]}','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','history_development_aeronautics'),
	 ('0f01d7ad-0ed4-4a80-b070-4f7f81373037'::uuid,'SIN2Α THEORY','MODEL','{}','A hypothesis proposed that suggested a certain relationship between lift and angle of attack, possibly supported but refuted by various tests conducted over different years.','{}','{}','{"frequency": 1, "text_unit_ids": ["16d966814983125a6e32b061e1707e94f1e8d9d91c7fb8fece809b8d03586b149afc62f017609bda9a3a36cbfcdfd60df5527110c12c82e5fcd08b8eb20847b0"]}','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','history_development_aeronautics');

The contraction ratio refers to the reduction in cross-sectional area between the fan or compressor section and the working section of the tunnel. By narrowing this initial section, the design prevents the creation of significant pressure waves and turbulence at the entrance. This optimized aerodynamic approach ensures that as air moves from the high-velocity region towards the lower velocity conditions in the test section, it remains smooth and consistent.

These improvements are essential for obtaining accurate and reliable data when testing various models or objects within the wind tunnel. The uniformity','{}','{}','{"frequency": 2, "text_unit_ids": ["653aa46087e791b134dbbd802cc7f2be070fd13ba9b27acc8585793069a21cb0efa3b5f8653b3d05323cc3ed759a463b78204a2bc4749488e28d38de3050a9cc", "653aa46087e791b134dbbd802cc7f2be070fd13ba9b27acc8585793069a21cb0efa3b5f8653b3d05323cc3ed759a463b78204a2bc4749488e28d38de3050a9cc"]}','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','history_development_aeronautics');

These comprehensive fan components are essential for maintaining consistent airflow throughout both tunnels, contributing to their operational effectiveness. The use of a gas engine驱动的风扇组件在Kernot78隧道中的应用进一步强调了这些组件的重要性，并为隧道系统的高效运行和安全性提供了坚实保障。','{}','{}','{"frequency": 2, "text_unit_ids": ["9b04b65904320d152e1a24cfa860cad23a1e8cf8a6b3402f1434285bed985ebbf31d5bfe08c052a7e873eb3dccd9ad3800832d2194ca94adad02b5f4b8043f99", "af0b7dc953d20f99423204bc6976714fb8bc794b04cf5ce8101cfceef20985a957bc6eca2691ec075aaa01420b302e2b2b0c8d5a5c0d508a6dabb65c91d84d5a"]}','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','history_development_aeronautics'),
	 ('80a6e57e-c2c3-4197-9453-7c097df548a8'::uuid,'ASYMMETRIC IRREGULAR SHAPE DUCT','MECHANISM','{}','Irregular-shaped duct through which a circular axial flow was turned at a right angle, then converged to a higher velocity square jet in Kernot78''s experiment.<|','{}','{}','{"frequency": 1, "text_unit_ids": ["9b04b65904320d152e1a24cfa860cad23a1e8cf8a6b3402f1434285bed985ebbf31d5bfe08c052a7e873eb3dccd9ad3800832d2194ca94adad02b5f4b8043f99"]}','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','history_development_aeronautics');

