	 ('39c5d4dd-e0ce-4779-8888-19dc1c8f2ad2'::uuid,'EILMER OF MALMESBURY''S FLYING MACHINE','DEVICE','{}','Eilmer of Malmesbury''s flying machine, conceived around 1010 CE, represents a pioneering attempt in aviation history. Although not successful due to limitations in available materials and knowledge of aerodynamics of the time, this prototype significantly influenced subsequent developments in flight technology. Eilmer’s visionary design served as an inspiration for later inventors, illustrating early human aspirations towards flight and contributing to the evolution of aviation theory and practice.','{}','{}','{"frequency": 2, "text_unit_ids": ["46b667214423448900a64449a21a8d78137e40dbbcde1ff7361b13892626a596937541e8a1dff8c28756c1af322bcfde1298239045005d93a04cd46043247c20", "46b667214423448900a64449a21a8d78137e40dbbcde1ff7361b13892626a596937541e8a1dff8c28756c1af322bcfde1298239045005d93a04cd46043247c20"]}','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','history_development_aeronautics'),
	 ('f2704b01-8284-44a0-a565-e0d6a33306aa'::uuid,'WINGS ATTACHED TO THE BODY','MECHANISM','{}','Used as a parachute for soft landing after the gunpowder was spent during the rocket flight','{}','{}','{"frequency": 3, "text_unit_ids": ["624b0f2e5156161ffdb09c558f32b39ad0bf347e1dcc51d0cc803eb1592f75125b51005c9a82dfcfa9afb96df74b8311d90272937604af08308a19e41b14f3c5", "624b0f2e5156161ffdb09c558f32b39ad0bf347e1dcc51d0cc803eb1592f75125b51005c9a82dfcfa9afb96df74b8311d90272937604af08308a19e41b14f3c5", "624b0f2e5156161ffdb09c558f32b39ad0bf347e1dcc51d0cc803eb1592f75125b51005c9a82dfcfa9afb96df74b8311d90272937604af08308a19e41b14f3c5"]}','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','history_development_aeronautics'),
	 ('f6e9fa6d-9325-446a-90ff-f2169673b52b'::uuid,'MONTGOLFIER BROTHERS'' HOT-AIR BALLOON','DEVICE','{}','Developed by Joseph Montgolfier and Jacques-Etienne Montgolfier, first publicly demonstrated human flight in Paris 1783 using this hot-air balloon.>','{}','{}','{"frequency": 3, "text_unit_ids": ["624b0f2e5156161ffdb09c558f32b39ad0bf347e1dcc51d0cc803eb1592f75125b51005c9a82dfcfa9afb96df74b8311d90272937604af08308a19e41b14f3c5", "624b0f2e5156161ffdb09c558f32b39ad0bf347e1dcc51d0cc803eb1592f75125b51005c9a82dfcfa9afb96df74b8311d90272937604af08308a19e41b14f3c5", "624b0f2e5156161ffdb09c558f32b39ad0bf347e1dcc51d0cc803eb1592f75125b51005c9a82dfcfa9afb96df74b8311d90272937604af08308a19e41b14f3c5"]}','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','history_development_aeronautics'),
	 ('987a532c-638f-4a41-8f71-780aaa9fca7b'::uuid,'AIRSHIP','DEVICE','{}','The entity "AIRSHIP" refers to a powered heavier-than-air craft, which evolved significantly during the technological advancements of the 1800s. Early forms of airships were described by inventors such as Giffard and Forlanini. These early airships were steerable and featured powered propulsion, setting the stage for the development of later dirigibles. The term encompasses a progression from the initial concept to more sophisticated designs that combined steerability with powered flight, marking a pivotal era in the history of aviation technology.','{}','{}','{"frequency": 5, "text_unit_ids": ["624b0f2e5156161ffdb09c558f32b39ad0bf347e1dcc51d0cc803eb1592f75125b51005c9a82dfcfa9afb96df74b8311d90272937604af08308a19e41b14f3c5", "624b0f2e5156161ffdb09c558f32b39ad0bf347e1dcc51d0cc803eb1592f75125b51005c9a82dfcfa9afb96df74b8311d90272937604af08308a19e41b14f3c5", "624b0f2e5156161ffdb09c558f32b39ad0bf347e1dcc51d0cc803eb1592f75125b51005c9a82dfcfa9afb96df74b8311d90272937604af08308a19e41b14f3c5", "b93603f69bb902d6bc4a15e32e34bac0942d14f58f5b7fd54e0187ddc73790c3986b6f906396ba733338823b8e99640c1794d84bcc0a8862b2e18fb964601739", "b93603f69bb902d6bc4a15e32e34bac0942d14f58f5b7fd54e0187ddc73790c3986b6f906396ba733338823b8e99640c1794d84bcc0a8862b2e18fb964601739"]}','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','history_development_aeronautics'),
	 ('25db4826-fd95-44f3-a822-817c72dbda99'::uuid,'RUBBER-BAND MOTOR','MECHANISM','{}','The RUBBER-BAND MOTOR is described as an alternative to both internal and external engines. This motor serves as a simpler and more controlled solution, offering an easier-to-manipulate method for generating mechanical energy compared to conventional engines, which may be powered by various means including chemical reactions like those involving gunpowder. The rubber-band motor thus provides a practical substitute that is likely less complex, potentially safer, and more straightforward to operate in educational or experimental settings where precision control is required.','{}','{}','{"frequency": 2, "text_unit_ids": ["faa334cc3a5b50c3cebcf1df46beb7be9ad777690802933a651dec6cbd0da34c9fef6dd95627eca4b6a746fc7c67bc72b217d1c4e60e92895dbfef4b8412f573", "faa334cc3a5b50c3cebcf1df46beb7be9ad777690802933a651dec6cbd0da34c9fef6dd95627eca4b6a746fc7c67bc72b217d1c4e60e92895dbfef4b8412f573"]}','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','history_development_aeronautics'),
	 ('ebd049f5-b471-4fae-be26-7f88265d54d5'::uuid,'ASPECT RATIO','MECHANISM','{}','The term "Aspect Ratio" is a characteristic that describes the relationship between the length and width of wings. This metric is crucial for comparing different wing designs with the aim of enhancing lift performance. The aspect ratio is often utilized in various aerodynamic studies, including Wenham''s wind tunnel tests, to assess and optimize flying objects such as airplanes, unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs), or other aircraft models. By analyzing this parameter, engineers can make informed decisions about wing design to improve efficiency and effectiveness in terms of lift generation while also considering factors like drag and structural integrity.','{}','{}','{"frequency": 2, "text_unit_ids": ["a1689fa4557c7bd9828498b6af22e4d56a6e70b706bc03a66df0ec58854f6cb93cfb6e67be14e6cf7954609e79e3b6bd423a0ba59422819f13f132672854041e", "a1689fa4557c7bd9828498b6af22e4d56a6e70b706bc03a66df0ec58854f6cb93cfb6e67be14e6cf7954609e79e3b6bd423a0ba59422819f13f132672854041e"]}','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','history_development_aeronautics'),
	 ('aa212d95-4ea7-413a-878d-27e681dde3be'::uuid,'ROYAL AERONAUTICAL SOCIETY OF GREAT BRITAIN','ORGANIZATION','{}','The Royal Aeronautical Society of Great Britain was established in 1866. This society played a pivotal role in advancing aerial and mechanical flight through academic research and presentations. Notably, John Joseph Waterston Wenham, an esteemed engineer, made significant contributions at this nascent stage by presenting his groundbreaking research on various engineering devices within the organization. These studies were instrumental in laying foundational principles that eventually led to the development of wind tunnels—a critical tool for aerodynamic testing. Consequently, the Society of Great Britain''s early support and Wenham''s pivotal presentations have solidified its legacy as a cornerstone institution in the field of aeronautics, contributing significantly to advancements in aviation technology over the subsequent decades.','{}','{}','{"frequency": 2, "text_unit_ids": ["a1689fa4557c7bd9828498b6af22e4d56a6e70b706bc03a66df0ec58854f6cb93cfb6e67be14e6cf7954609e79e3b6bd423a0ba59422819f13f132672854041e", "a1689fa4557c7bd9828498b6af22e4d56a6e70b706bc03a66df0ec58854f6cb93cfb6e67be14e6cf7954609e79e3b6bd423a0ba59422819f13f132672854041e"]}','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','history_development_aeronautics'),
	 ('6b03ab48-2850-4000-9adb-d24a2db2d424'::uuid,'BIPLANE','DEVICE','{}','"Biplane is a configuration with two overlapping wings; Chanute concluded it was more successful for gliders."<|','{}','{}','{"frequency": 2, "text_unit_ids": ["ccac1a178375331bc449ac2d2eec635f0983c00e6d254912345c012c0c41f3a9cc65da465cf715f8bc206801bb7f81cd82c005354ce5454c3970c507c2045930", "ccac1a178375331bc449ac2d2eec635f0983c00e6d254912345c012c0c41f3a9cc65da465cf715f8bc206801bb7f81cd82c005354ce5454c3970c507c2045930"]}','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','history_development_aeronautics');

