	 ('f75972b6-cc1d-4027-8b03-3e9ce8cd4a37'::uuid,'PARIS','GEO','{}','Paris, often associated with artistic and technological innovations of the past, was a pivotal location for the early history of aviation. Specifically, numerous hot-air balloon launches took place within its bounds during the late 18th century. These pioneering experiments contributed significantly to the development of aerostatic principles and inspired future generations of scientists and inventors in their quest for airborne travel.','{}','{}','{"frequency": 2, "text_unit_ids": ["5f6fd011c9ca704fc492591b733a486799017472d116244888b93e9d7d7bc92c33215f95b7a0a6f3c020f6ed022aa38e6f8f3044d9ae52a1e579de70fa928ad5", "5f6fd011c9ca704fc492591b733a486799017472d116244888b93e9d7d7bc92c33215f95b7a0a6f3c020f6ed022aa38e6f8f3044d9ae52a1e579de70fa928ad5"]}','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','2026-07-17 13:19:24.183818','history_development_aeronautics'),
