	 ('242a4bab-8653-4260-b044-eb2c6de3b21d'::uuid,'IDEAL GAS MODEL','MODEL','{}','The IDEAL GAS MODEL is a simplified representation often utilized in the study of gas dynamics, particularly where compressibility effects are important but thermal effects can be neglected. This model finds application in observing transonic motions, which occur when gases transition between subsonic and supersonic speeds without considering substantial changes in temperature.

While primarily focused on gas dynamics, this model is not confined to aerodynamic applications; it has broad utility in various scientific and engineering contexts due to its effectiveness in providing a clear understanding of certain flow behaviors. Its key strength lies in simplifying complex fluid characteristics for qualitative analysis, making it an invaluable tool for initial assessments or when quantitative accuracy is less critical than conceptual clarity.

