	 ('4ef92c8b-c091-4fa7-a8b3-09687a838098'::uuid,'STREAMTUBE OF VARIABLE CROSS-SECTION','DEVICE','{}','The entity "streamtube of variable cross-section" refers to an imagined streamline characterized by its varying sections, designed as a tool for studying the implications of Bernoulli’s equation. This streamtube is conceptualized to provide insights into fluid dynamics and pressure-velocity relationships within non-uniform flow scenarios. By examining different cross-sectional areas along the streamtube, researchers can explore how changes in these dimensions affect fluid behavior according to Bernoulli''s principles. The structure serves as a valuable model for understanding complex fluid flow phenomena, particularly where the relationship between pressure and velocity varies significantly across differing sections of the streamline.','{}','{}','{"frequency": 2, "text_unit_ids": ["b5612dfd5afd1a966867270904e7977f694cbe6e96b4be34a53c32ab6f48a581ba2e0825a6d9165aaeb6957d598461f699ff9ff6c7b4ff82bb2c2e2dba4929d9", "b5612dfd5afd1a966867270904e7977f694cbe6e96b4be34a53c32ab6f48a581ba2e0825a6d9165aaeb6957d598461f699ff9ff6c7b4ff82bb2c2e2dba4929d9"]}','2026-07-17 16:18:55.489892','2026-07-17 16:18:55.489892','aerodynamics_v1'),
